1. Animation & Motion
Framer Motion
• React‑first animation library, intuitive API for gestures, physics‑based transitions.
• Great for UI micro‑interactions, page transitions, mounting/unmounting effects.

GSAP (GreenSock Animation Platform)
• Ultra‑high‑performance timeline‑based animations (DOM, Canvas, SVG, WebGL).
• Ideal for complex sequences—think banner ads, interactive storytelling.

Motion One
• Lightweight, web‑standards‑based (Web Animations API) alternative to Framer Motion/GSAP.
• Sweet spot when bundle size is critical.

LottieFiles
• Renders Adobe After Effects animations exported as JSON via Bodymovin.
• Use for pre‑made “production‑ready” vector animations.

Rive
• Real‑time interactive vector animations with state machines.
• Perfect when you want user‑driven, dynamic animations (e.g. interactive mascots, games).

2. Page Transitions & Scroll
barba.js
• Smooth PJAX‑style page transitions.
• Hook into lifecycle events (enter/leave) to coordinate animations.

Lenis
• Smooth scrolling engine with inertia, easing controls.
• Use when default browser scroll feels too abrupt.

3. 3D & WebGL
three.js + raw WebGL
• three.js = high‑level wrapper on WebGL for 3D scenes (cameras, lights, meshes).
• Raw WebGL = ultimate control (steeper learning curve).

Spline
• Browser‑based 3D design tool & runtime.
• Great for designers to build 3D UIs and export embeddable scenes.

4. UI Component Libraries & Styling
Tailwind CSS
• Utility‑first CSS framework.
• Highly composable, minimal runtime.

daisyUI
• Tailwind plugin that adds ready‑made component classes (buttons, cards, navbars).

Ant Design
• Comprehensive React component library with polished look‑and‑feel.
• Includes form controls, data displays, layout grids.

shadcn/ui
• “Headless” primitives + pre‑built components on top of Radix + Tailwind.
• Great if you want consistent design tokens but still custom styling.

5. State, Data Fetching & Realtime
Redux
• Predictable global state container.
• Use with React‑Redux hooks for complex state logic.

TanStack Query (formerly React Query)
• Server‑state management (caching, retries, background refetch).
• Ideal for data fetching and synchronizing UI with API.

Liveblocks
• Realtime presence, cursors, collaborative editing primitives.
• Use when building collaborative apps (whiteboards, co‑editing).

6. Forms & Inputs
React Hook Form
• Performant, hook‑based form validation & state.
• Integrates nicely with UI libraries and schema validators (Yup, Zod).

7. Bundling & Tooling
Turbopack
• Next‑gen, Rust‑powered bundler from Vercel.
• Blazing fast incremental builds; alternative to Webpack.

8. Carousels & Sliders
Swiper.js
• Fully featured, touch‑enabled slider.
• Modular—only include the features you need (pagination, lazyload, thumbs).